Former Super Eagles of Nigeria captain, Austin ‘Jay Jay’ Okocha, has named the country he will be watching at this year’s World Cup. Okocha singled out Senegal as the team to keep an eye on, following the draw for the 2022 World Cup on Friday. The African champions are in Group A alongside shots Qatar, Ecuador and The Netherlands. Okocha was asked if an African country can finally win the trophy this time around. The former PSG and Bolton Wanderers midfielder replied: “We have come a long way. We will see how it goes this year. When pressed further on which team he will have his eyes on, Okocha replied: “Senegal”.